# PHP Login System - Security Awareness Project

## Overview

This project is a simple web-based login system built using PHP, MySQL, HTML, and XAMPP.  
It is designed for cybersecurity learning and demonstrates common web vulnerabilities such as SQL Injection and Cross-Site Scripting (XSS), along with their secure fixes.

This project is part of cybersecurity practice for understanding how attackers exploit weak authentication systems and how to prevent them.

---

## Topics Covered

* Basic Login System using PHP
* Client-Server Communication (POST Method)
* SQL Injection Attack Simulation
* Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Basics
* Secure Coding Practices
* Prepared Statements in PHP
* Database Connectivity using MySQL

---

## Features

* Simple login form interface
* Backend authentication using PHP
* MySQL database integration
* Vulnerable version (for learning attacks)
* Secure version (with protection implemented)
* Attack payload testing support

---

## Tools Used

* XAMPP (Apache + MySQL)
* PHP
* MySQL
* HTML
* VS Code

---

